# Git commits and pushes — no agent co-author

When the user asks you to `git commit`, `git push`, or create a PR:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by:` trailers naming Cursor, Cursor Agent, `cursoragent`, or any AI/agent identity.
- **Never** use `--author` (or similar flags) to attribute the commit to an agent.
- Commit messages must contain **only** the user-facing summary (via HEREDOC); no co-author footers.
- **Before committing**, run `bash scripts/install-git-hooks.sh` if `.git/hooks/commit-msg` is missing (Cursor injects co-author lines automatically).
- **After committing**, verify: `git log -1 --format=%B` must not contain `Co-authored-by` or `cursoragent`. If it does, `git commit --amend -m "$(cat <<'EOF' ... EOF')"` with the same message only (no co-author), then push.

The commit author must remain the user only.
